The paper focuses on community detection in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), social and economic systems (cs.SOC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The proposed method also involves similarity-based clustering, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses experimental results to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
